init_text:
Are We Being Bad Citizens If We Don't Keep Up With the News?

In your opinion, are we being bad citizens if we don't keep up with the news? Do you think all people have some responsibility to know what is going on in the world? Does engaging with current events actually do anything at all? Why do you think the way you do?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: There are some people who don't, and that's fine.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: A few times it does feel like the news will depress me all day, because everything seems so broken.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It's all their political agendas, and most will try to manipulate you into agreeing with them.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I'm not sure how we can move forward until we can get people to stop being afraid of each other.
